detail: Brandon James Keener is an American actor, living in Los Angeles, California. He was born and raised in Fort Smith, Arkansas[1] and graduated from University of Arkansas at Fayetteville, where he won an Irene Ryan scholarship for collegiate actors and performed at the Kennedy Center.
